elements.name: Page2Instructions
elements.html: Introduction: This assessment includes a brief physical exam along with some photos [if photos are to be taken during telehealth]. I'll also ask some questions about your child's [or your (if self-reporting)] physical development along with some family history questions.

elements.name: RDS_5
elements.title: Is there any family history of developmental disabilities like intellectual disability or autism for example?

elements.name: RDS_6
elements.title: Is there any family history of differences in the  structure of the body (malformations, birth defects) like cleft palate, heart defects, or spina bifida for example?

elements.name: RDS_7
elements.title:
Are you and the child's other biological parent related in anyway?

OR

[If non biological caregiver is informant ask:] Are the biological parents related in anyway?

elements.name: RDS_18
elements.title: Birth Head Circumference, Date Measurement Obtained

elements.name: RDS_22
elements.title: Most Recent Weight, Date Measurement Obtained

elements.name: RDS_26
elements.title: Most Recent Height, Date Measurement Obtained

elements.name: RDS_29
elements.title: Most Recent Head Circumference Standard Deviation

elements.name: RDS_30
elements.title: Most Recent Head Circumference, Date Measurement Obtained

elements.name: RDS_31_OTHER
elements.title: Other Most Recent Head Circumference Source

elements.name: RDS_32
elements.title: Which biological parents were present at appointment?

elements.name: RDS_33
elements.title: Does the patient appear dysmorphic or unusual compared to the biological parents?

elements.name: RDS_34
elements.title: Ask parent / caregiver - "Do you think he /she has unusual facial features that are not in keeping with the family?"

elements.name: RDS_36
elements.title:
Skin (select all that apply)

Ask patient/parent - Are there any birth marks, café au lait spots, ash leaf spots, or skin lesions? If yes, photograph if needed.

choices.text: Normal (absent of any lesions, marks, spots, etc.)
Brachycephaly (AP dimension /length compared to width appears shortened; head shape looks flattened)
Dolichocephaly (AP length of head compared to width appears increased; head shape looks long)
Abnormal Hair Whorl (the hair whorl is the single point on the scalp, normally in the midline and close to the vertex, where hair growth arises)

elements.name: RDS_39
elements.title: Eyes and Periorbital Region (select all that apply)

choices.text: Deep-set Eyes (in profile: eyes that are more deeply recessed into the plane of the face than is typical)
Synophrys (meeting of the medial eyebrows in the midline)

elements.name: RDS_39_OTHER
elements.title: Other Eyes and Periorbital Region Description

elements.name: RDS_40
elements.title: Ears (select all that apply)
elements.description: Examples: Abnormal form (Stahl's ear, pointed), Abnormal form (cleft lobe), Abnormal form (attached lobe)

choices.text: Abnormal Location/Position (for example, ears appear low set)

elements.name: RDS_41
elements.title: Nose and Philtrum (select all that apply)
elements.description: Examples: Long Philtrum, Short, Abnormal nasal bridge (depressed)

choices.text: Abnormal Mouth (oral cavity including hard and soft palate, and the tongue)

elements.name: RDS_43
elements.title: Hands/Fingers/Nails (select all that apply)
elements.description: Examples: Tapered Fingers, Abnormal palmer crease (deep), Abnormal palmar crease (single transverse crease)
